</head>
<body>
    <!-- Include the header here -->
    <%- include("header.ejs") %>

    <!-- Community Favourite content start here -->
    <div class="community-favourite-container">
        <h1>Community Favourite Recipes</h1>
        <div class="recipe-grid">
            <!-- Recipe 1 -->
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/telerpita.jpg" alt="Teler Pita">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Teler Pita</h3>
                    <p> Teler Pitha is known for its distinctive taste, combining the sweetness of molasses with the subtlety of coconut. The frying process gives it a crispy outer layer while the inside remains soft and chewy. This contrast in textures makes it a favorite among both children and adults.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Recipe 2 -->
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/jilapi.jpg.webp" alt="Jilapi">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Jilapi</h3>
                    <p>ilapi is known for its crisp outer layer and juicy, syrup-soaked interior. The combination of the fried batter's crunch and the sweet, sticky syrup creates a delightful texture contrast that is both satisfying and indulgent.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Recipe 3 -->
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/naksi pitha.jpg" alt="Naksi pitha">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Naksi Pitha</h3>
                    <p>Nakshi Pitha is a testament to the artistry and culinary skills of Bengali women, who traditionally make these pithas at home. The process of creating these delicacies is often a communal activity, bringing together family members across generations. It is particularly popular during winter festivals like Nabanna, which celebrates the new harvest, and during the Bengali New Year (Pohela Boishakh).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/Mughlai-Paratha.jpg.webp" alt="Mughlai Parotha">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Mughlai PorothaS</h3>
                    <p>Mughlai Paratha is a treat for the senses, with its crispy, golden exterior and flavorful, juicy filling. The combination of spiced minced meat and eggs, along with the crispy paratha, creates a delightful mix of textures and flavors. Each bite offers a rich, savory taste that is both satisfying and indulgent.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/chitoi pita.jpg" alt="Chitoi pitha">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Chitoi Pitha</h3>
                    <p>Chitoi Pitha has a mild, slightly sweet flavor with a soft and spongy texture. The simplicity of the ingredients allows it to pair well with a variety of toppings and sides. The contrast between the slightly crispy bottom and the soft top adds to its unique appeal.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/patisaptapita.jpg" alt="PatiSapta pitha">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Patisapta Pitha</h3>
                    <p>The texture of Patisapta Pitha is one of its most appealing aspects. The outer crepe is soft, thin, and slightly elastic, similar to a delicate pancake. When cooked to perfection, it has a slight crispness at the edges that gives way to a tender bite. Inside, the filling is smooth and creamy, often with a slight graininess from the grated coconut or a luscious consistency from the khoya. This combination of the soft, pliable crepe and the rich, textured filling creates a delightful mouthfeel that is both comforting and satisfying.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/panta_Ilish.jpg" alt="Panta Ilish">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Panta Ilish</h3>
                    <p>The fermented rice, or panta bhat, has a refreshing, tangy flavor that pairs perfectly with the rich, savory taste of Hilsa fish. The slight sourness of the rice complements the fish's natural oiliness, creating a balanced and harmonious taste. The accompaniments add layers of flavor, from the sharpness of raw onions to the heat of green chilies and the pungent kick of mustard paste.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/Jhalmuri.jpg.webp" alt="Naksi pitha">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Naksi Pitha</h3>
                    <p>Jhalmuri is a quintessential Bengali snack that captures the essence of street food with its bold flavors and diverse textures. It is a snack that is easy to prepare, making it a popular choice for quick bites and social gatherings. Whether enjoyed on a bustling street corner or at home with a cup of tea, jhalmuri remains a beloved treat that embodies the vibrant culinary culture of Bengal.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/doi.webp" alt="doi">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Doi</h3>
                    <p>The natural fermentation process gives plain doi a mildly tangy
                         flavor, which can range from subtle to pronounced depending on 
                         the fermentation time and temperature. Mishti doi, on the other 
                         hand, is sweet and has a caramel-like richness due to the added sugar 
                         or jaggery.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="recipe-item">
                <img src="images/Falooda.jpg.webp" alt="Falooda">
                <div>
                    <h3 onclick="toggleDescription(this)">Falooda</h3>
                    <p>The dessert combines the sweetness of rose syrup and milk with the floral notes of the rose. The ice cream adds a creamy richness, while the basil seeds provide a subtle, refreshing flavor.
                    Falooda is known for its diverse textures. The vermicelli is soft and slightly chewy, the basil seeds are gelatinous and slippery, and the ice cream is smooth and creamy. The addition of nuts and fruit provides a crunchy and juicy contrast, making each bite a delightful adventure.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Include the Footer here -->
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Recipe Oasis. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
    
    
    <script>
        function toggleDescription(element) {
            const description = element.nextElementSibling;
            if (description.style.display === "none" || description.style.display === "") {
                description.style.display = "block";
            } else {
                description.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
